📄 src/App.tsx
Task 1 & 3: State Declarations
Add these state hooks within the App component, specifically near other UI-related state (e.g., after invGenerated): // Task 1: State for tracking views
const [freeViewsUsed, setFreeViewsUsed] = useState(0);

// Task 3: Contractor info for invoice
const [invContractorName, setInvContractorName] = useState('');
const [invPhone, setInvPhone] = useState('');
const [invEmail, setInvEmail] = useState('');

// Task 5: Blueprint / Backlog state
const [blueprintIdeas, setBlueprintIdeas] = useState([]);
const [newIdea, setNewIdea] = useState('');
const [selectedPhase, setSelectedPhase] = useState('Phase 1');           - task 1 = Task 1: Logic Update
In the startScan() function, find setScanComplete(true); and update it: setScanComplete(true);
setFreeViewsUsed(v => Math.min(3, v + 1)); - Task 3: Invoice Form & Generator
1. Form Update: Add these three fields at the top of your invoice form container, before the "Client Name" field:<div className="space-y-4 mb-6 border-b border-slate-700 pb-6">
  <input 
    type="text" 
    placeholder="Your name / company" 
    className="w-full bg-slate-800 border border-slate-700 p-2 rounded"
    value={invContractorName}
    onChange={(e) => setInvContractorName(e.target.value)}
  />
  <input 
    type="text" 
    placeholder="Your phone" 
    className="w-full bg-slate-800 border border-slate-700 p-2 rounded"
    value={invPhone}
    onChange={(e) => setInvPhone(e.target.value)}
  />
  <input 
    type="email" 
    placeholder="Your email" 
    className="w-full bg-slate-800 border border-slate-700 p-2 rounded"
    value={invEmail}
    onChange={(e) => setInvEmail(e.target.value)}
  />
</div>2. Invoice Output: Within the invoice document component:

Add a 4px top bar: <div className="h-1 w-full bg-high-vis-orange mb-8" />

Replace the FROM column header:<div className="flex flex-col">
  <span className="font-bold text-lg">{invContractorName || 'Your Company'}</span>
  <span className="text-sm text-slate-400">{invPhone} | {invEmail}</span>
  <span className="text-xs font-medium text-high-vis-orange mt-1">JobFilter — Built For Trades</span>
</div>            ------------------Payment Due Date: Add a field showing new Date(Date.now() + 12096e5).toLocaleDateString() (14 days from now).

Upsell Tip: Remove the current bg-high-vis-orange/10 block and place it below your "Print Invoice" buttons. ------------ Task 4: Landing Page Refresh
Locate the <header id="features"> and update the text nodes:<h1 className="text-4xl font-black uppercase">STOP QUOTING FOR FREE.</h1>
<p className="text-xl text-slate-400 mt-4 max-w-2xl">
  JobFilter sits in front of your WhatsApp. Demands photos and postcodes. 
  Charges tyre-kickers a Priority Booking deposit before they ever reach your phone.
</p>
<div className="mt-8 flex gap-4">
  <button className="bg-high-vis-orange text-black px-6 py-3 font-bold">Find Jobs Near Me →</button>
  <button className="border border-slate-700 px-6 py-3 font-bold">See How It Works</button>
</div> ---- Task 5: Blueprint Section (Firebase)
1. Navigation: Add this to your desktop nav:
<a href="#blueprint" className="hover:text-high-vis-orange transition-colors">Blueprint</a>

2. Section Implementation: Add this after the #tools section: <section id="blueprint" className="py-20 border-t border-slate-800">
  <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 className="text-3xl font-black mb-2 uppercase">THE BLUEPRINT</h2>
    <p className="text-slate-400 mb-8">Public roadmap and feature dump. No password required.</p>

    {/* Input Block */}
    <div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 mb-12">
      <input 
        type="text" 
        placeholder="e.g. Material Fetcher AI..." 
        className="flex-1 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-700 p-3 rounded"
        value={newIdea}
        onChange={(e) => setNewIdea(e.target.value)}
      />
      <select 
        className="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-700 p-3 rounded"
        value={selectedPhase}
        onChange={(e) => setSelectedPhase(e.target.value)}
      >
        <option>Phase 1</option>
        <option>Phase 2</option>
        <option>Phase 3</option>
      </select>
      <button 
        onClick={async () => {
          if(!newIdea) return;
          await addDoc(collection(db, "blueprint"), {
            idea: newIdea,
            phase: selectedPhase,
            createdAt: serverTimestamp()
          });
          setNewIdea('');
        }}
        className="bg-high-vis-orange text-black font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded"
      >
        LOG IDEA
      </button>
    </div>

    {/* Backlog */}
    <h3 className="text-xl font-bold mb-4 uppercase text-slate-500">THE BACKLOG</h3>
    <div className="grid gap-4">
      {blueprintIdeas.map((item) => (
        <div key={item.id} className="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded border border-slate-800 flex justify-between items-center">
          <div>
            <span className="text-xs font-bold uppercase px-2 py-1 bg-slate-800 rounded mr-3 text-high-vis-orange">
              {item.phase}
            </span>
            <span className="text-lg">{item.idea}</span>
          </div>
          <button 
            onClick={() => deleteDoc(doc(db, "blueprint", item.id))}
            className="text-slate-600 hover:text-red-500 transition-colors px-2"
          >
            ✕
          </button>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section> ------------ 3. Firebase Sync Logic: Add this useEffect inside the App component: useEffect(() => {
  const q = query(collection(db, "blueprint"), orderBy("createdAt", "desc"));
  const unsubscribe = onSnapshot(q, (snapshot) => {
    setBlueprintIdeas(snapshot.docs.map(doc => ({ id: doc.id, ...doc.data() })));
  });
  return () => unsubscribe();
}, []); -------------------- 🎨 index.css
Update the theme block to remove the old color:/* Remove this line */
--color-electric-cyan: #00f2ff;

/* Ensure this is defined for Task 2 classes */
--color-high-vis-orange: #ff6b00;

